        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          This fixture would more be likely to end up in a West Ham win if it was being played at the Bridge. When they're at home it seems to me they don't actually have a set plan. Away to Arsenal, City & Liverpool it was simple. They knew they were going to have 40% of the ball top whack (actually averaged 34.2% in those 3 games) so had to stay defensively rigid, be aggressive in the dangerous defensive areas and look to counter. They have done it well thus far and are actually top of the league on away performances. At home, however, where their fans demand they make the running- even against the top teams, they struggle. Statistically they are pretty much the same home & away (slightly more possession) but they don't look half as dangerous and seem to me to be caught in two minds. They don't have the midfield to really control the game but they have the home pressure telling them to try to. If they use their away plan here then they could win, if not then I fancy Chelsea by a couple.
